# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHITELIST .gitignore for the Paper_replication project
#
# This folder contains ~300 GB of licensed data (OptionMetrics/IvyDB, CRSP)
# and copyrighted papers that MUST NOT be uploaded to GitHub.
#
# Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING by default, then explicitly allow only the
# source code and documentation. This guarantees no data file is ever
# committed by accident.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1) Ignore everything
*

# 2) But still descend into subfolders (so allowed files below are found)
!*/

# 3) Allow source code and documentation
!.gitignore
!*.R
!*.r
!*.Rmd
!*.qmd
!*.md
!*.csv
!*.txt
!*.py
!*.do
!*.sql

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4) Safety net: re-ignore data / large / generated files even if one of the
#    extensions above would otherwise catch them.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.parquet
*.duckdb
*.duckdb.tmp
*.duckdb.wal
*.rds
*.RData
*.rda
*.pdf
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.html
*.docx
*.xlsx
*.textClipping
.DS_Store
.Rapp.history
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rproj.user/

# Temp / scratch folders
*.tmp/
.tmp/
**/duckdb_temp_*
